sAuthor: Sanchez-Russinyol, M. d. C.[Maria del Carmen]
Citation.sTitle: Isobaric vapor liquid equilibrium for ternary mixtures of ethanol and methylcyclohexane with 3-methylpentane and tert-butyl alcohol at 101.3 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Consistent vapor liquid equilibrium (VLE) data for the ternary systems 3-methylpentane + ethanol + methylcyclohexane and ethanol + tert-butyl  alcohol (TBA) + methylcyclohexane are reported at 101.3 kPa. The VLE data have been correlated by Wilson, UNIQUAC and NRTL equations.  The ternary systems do not present azeotrope and are well predicted from binary interaction parameters.
